Job Descriptions









Transmission Function Employees—Job Titles and Descriptions:System Operations Supervisor Performs the leadership duties of a real time operations supervisor, directing a team of employees in the routine and emergency monitoring and control of transmission and distribution systems and the dispatching of substation, field and trouble crews on electric system and customer outage complaints. This position has the explicit responsibility and authority to independently take actions necessary to ensure personnel safety and system reliability in accordance with other operating procedures and PJM emergency procedures/directives. Ensures coordination of Bulk Power activities with PJM, Mirant, and PPR Generation and Dispatch facilities and with neighboring utility companies.Senior System OperatorDirects and oversees the operation of the Bulk Power System, ensuring the safe, reliable and efficient operation of corporate assets. Monitors, controls and coordinates the Bulk Power System. Coordinates and monitors operations with PJM, Generation and Dispatch companies, and field personnel. This position has explicit responsibility and authority to independently take actions necessary to ensure personnel safety and system reliability in accordance with other operating procedures and PJM emergency procedures/directives.




























