Shared Facilities









Transmission function employees and marketing function employees of PHI are not housed in the same work location. There are several locations where both types of employees may be required to frequent from time to time in order to fulfill certain job and corporate responsibilities.Edison Place701 Ninth Street, NWWashington, D.C. 20068Office Building that houses many support services. The building also has a number of large conference rooms that are used for corporate meetings. King Street5th Floor800 King StreetWilmington, DE 19801Office Building that houses many support services. The building also has a number of large conference rooms that are used for corporate meetings.New Castle Regional Office (NCRO)401 Eagle Run RoadNewark, DE 19702There are utility marketing function employees located at NCRO. The building also has a number of large conference rooms that are used for corporate meetings.Atlantic Regional Office (Mays Landing)5100 Harding HighwayMays Landing, NJ 08330The building also has a number of large conference rooms that are used for corporate meetings.Computer FacilitiesPepco, Atlantic City Electric and Delmarva Power have shared computer networks that have password protections. To the extent transmission information is on those networks, access to the transmission information is available only to those employees granted access by the Chief Compliance Officer.The Pepco corporate computer system is located at the Pepco Control Center. Employees that maintain that system have been trained not to act as a conduit for transmission information.Fleet ServicesAs necessary, employees that perform transmission functions and those that perform marketing functions may request the use of company vehicles for local travel.




























