CategoriesWhen the government intends to acquire goods or services, it identifies the NAICS code that describes the principal purpose of that procurement. NAICS is production oriented (not product oriented) and categorizes businesses with others that have similar methods of production.







Products/ServicesProduct and Service Codes (PSC) describe products, services, and research and development purchased by the federal government.







