ShareContractsBy Year

The federal government obligated Pepco Energy Services, Inc. a high of $69.5 million USD in FY2007 and low of $3.46 million USD in FY2012. On average, it received $6,628,220 United States dollars in contract obligations per fiscal year.* Dollars Obligated: The amount of money obligated towards a vendor by a federal agency or agencies to work on a contract.* Base and All Options (Ceiling): The maximum amount that can be awarded to a contract as mutually agreed upon by the vendor and agency.



